We then consider a Landsberg setup that combines both positive illumination and negative illumination, as shown in Fig. 4g. The cell is in good thermal contact with the ambient environment at 300 K. In this case, the maximum work that can be extracted by this system is 1648.2 Wm−2, corresponding to an efficiency of η=ẆfσTs4=102.89%\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
