				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\eta = \frac{{\dot W}}{{f\sigma T_{\mathrm{s}}^4}} = 102.89\%$$\end{document}. It should be noted that this efficiency exceeds 100% as a portion of the power is obtained through the outgoing thermal radiation from the ambient to outer space. Nevertheless, the maximum work here significantly exceeds the established limit that is achievable by using only the sun or outer space as a thermodynamic resource, highlighting the importance of simultaneous energy harvesting from the sun and the cold universe.

